==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: A cappella
<hw>A cap*pel"la</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[It. See
<er>Chapel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>In church or
chapel style; -- said of compositions sung in the old church style,
without instrumental accompaniment; <as>as, a mass <ex>a capella</ex>,
i. e., a mass purely vocal</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A time
indication, equivalent to <xex>alla breve</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acapsular</ent>⟦br⟧
